This classic origami boat is folded from a square sheet of paper, presenting a variation of the traditional model.

It is based on *“La Barca”*, documented by Francisco Blanch in *Trabajos Manuales y Juegos Infantiles*, and sourced from [Origami Heaven.](%5Bhttps://www.origamiheaven.com/historytrabajosmanualeyjuegosinfantiles.htm%5D\(https://www.origamiheaven.com/historytrabajosmanualeyjuegosinfantiles.htm\))

Understanding the original diagram was particularly challenging due to its condensed and unconventional style, with minimal guidance and complex transitions between steps.

![reference (https://www.origamiheaven.com/history/Blanch%20Trabajos%20Manuales%20y%20Juegos%20Infantiles/Trabajos%20Manuales%20a.jpg)](/diagram-images/classic-origami-boat-square-version/image.png)

This work represents a careful reinterpretation of the original folding sequence, aiming to preserve its historical essence while improving clarity and readability.
